---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout title="Safeguarding">
  <div class="prose-bfs">
    <h2>Safeguarding Statement</h2>
    <p>
      Bright Futures School is committed to safeguarding and promoting the welfare of all pupils. We expect all staff, volunteers, and visitors to share this commitment.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our safeguarding and child protection policies and procedures are in accordance with national and local guidance, and are reviewed annually.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you have a concern about a child, please contact the school directly or report it to the appropriate authority.
    </p>

    <h2>Local Safeguarding Services — Oldham</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://www.oldham.gov.uk/info/200500/early_help" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Early Help (Oldham)</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.oldham.gov.uk/info/200543/send" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Local SEND Support (Oldham)</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.oldham.gov.uk/info/200543/send/2077/oldham_sendiass" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SENDIASS (Oldham)</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>National Helplines</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Channel Helpline: <a href="tel:02073407264">020 7340 7264</a></li>
      <li>Extremism Helpline: <a href="tel:02073407264">020 7340 7264</a></li>
      <li>Anti-Terrorist Helpline: <a href="tel:08007899321">0800 789 321</a></li>
      <li>NSPCC Helpline: <a href="tel:08088005000">0808 800 5000</a></li>
      <li>Operation Encompass: <a href="tel:02045139990">0204 513 9990</a></li>
      <li>Forced Marriage Unit: <a href="tel:02070080151">020 7008 0151</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>CEOP — Click to Report Online Abuse</h2>
    <p>
      If you are worried about online sexual abuse or the way someone has been communicating with a child online, you can make a report to CEOP:
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://www.ceop.police.uk/Safety-Centre/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <img src="/images/badges/ceop-click.gif" alt="Click CEOP — report online child abuse" class="h-16" />
      </a>
    </p>

    <h2>Allegations — September 2024</h2>
    <p>
      A statement from Zoe Thompson, Head of Development and Proprietor, regarding allegations made on social media (September 2024): Bright Futures School takes all concerns about the welfare of pupils extremely seriously. If you have any concerns about the welfare of a child in our care, we would urge you to report them through the appropriate channels — to the school directly, to Oldham Children's Services, or to Ofsted. We do not consider social media an appropriate or effective route for safeguarding concerns, and we will always address properly-made concerns promptly and transparently.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our full Safeguarding and Child Protection Policy is available on the <a href="/parents/policies">Policies page</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
